Our Staff


 


	Dentist in Boynton Beach, FL

	Our staff is committed to providing both personal care and expertise in your treatment. The descriptions below are designed to familiarize you with our staff.

Ronald Murstein 
	Dr. Ronald Murstein is a native of Boston, Massachusetts. He graduated cum laude from Clark University in Worcester. Mass. Graduating from the University of Pennsylvania School of Dental Medicine in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, Dr. Murstein trained for three years while serving his country in the U.S. Air Force at Andrews Air Force Base in Washington D.C. He moved to Florida in 1980 and established his practice in Boynton Beach in 1982 practicing at the same location since then.

	Over the years Dr. Murstein has been very involved in organized dentistry and continuing education. He is a member of the American Dental Association, the Florida Dental Association and the South Palm Beach County Dental Association. Dr. Murstein has been very involved at the Atlantic Research Dental Clinic in Lake Worth where he took many hours of continuing education. He served both as President of the Research Clinic and head of the Oral Diagnosis Clinic for a number of years. Recently, Dr. Murstein has been taking continuing education at Nova Southeastern University Dental School in Davie, Florida. This year alone he took courses in head and neck anatomy and dissection, periodontal surgery, pharmacology, and the diagnosis and treatment of Temporomandibular Joint Disorder (TMJ or TMD). In addition, he took courses in implant dentistry at Implant Seminars both in surgery and restoration. Dr. Murstein believes in staying current with modern dentistry but also feels his patients should not be "guinea pigs" for procedures, materials and techniques that are brought to the market by manufacturers before they are properly proven and tested in the "real" world.

	Dr. Murstein is married to Marjorie Brodsky, also from Boston. They have raised three wonderful children, Jonathan, Alyssa and Robert. Dr. Murstein is a passionate golfer (many time club champion on both courses at Broken Sound), an avid tennis player, skier, and sports enthusiast. He and Margie enjoy "cruising" together and are active in their synagogue.









	  









